Just a few highlights of 2022 💖

- Going to @rupaulsdragcon and getting to spend time with @hoodratdiego
- Winning Miss Lady @misscomedyqueen and reigning alongside my sister @mrmsadrien
- Headlining @austindragfest and an all AFAB drag revue at @c4nwa
- Celebrating my 30th birthday at @cocktailsandscreams 
- Going to @horrornightsorl with my friends countless times
- Performing at @revolutionlive with @thewakashame and @dollya.black and my mom coming out to see the show
- Doing my first show with @richweirdoescast, shortly followed by my second and third
- Taking up puppetry and ventriloquism with @magentathemonster 

Honorable Mentions (ie amazing experiences that I wanted to share but didn't have photos in drag):
- Seeing @catsthemusical live for the first time
- Visiting New York to see my sister @ettapuss and meeting her cat @marvelousmrsmatzo 
- Seeing the Jim Henson Exhibition at @movingimagenyc, the @amnh, and @strangeloopbway on Broadway
- Moving to a new house with my best friends (still in progress)
- Performing at @holidaymatsuri as Frankie Stein (my favorite cosplay to date!)
- Getting my first BJD for Christmas
- Making personal social media accounts and exploring my hobbies outside of drag

Our existence is resistance 🏳️‍🌈

A drag queen and a furry may be the last duo you'd expect to see at Orlando City Hall, but we're here for a good cause! Our self-expression is not a crime, an agenda, or a s*xual act. It's art, it's entertainment, and it's our first amendment right to be here; protesting legislation that aims to harm, and even eradicate, the most vulnerable in our community.

Check out @liberationorlando to learn more about anti-trans legislation in Florida and how you can get involved in the fight against it 🏳️‍⚧️

A message from @richweirdoescast:

As Florida's bill banning drag shows now sits on the governor's desk to be signed into law, we are painfully aware of how this will impact our cast and our beloved community. As vague as the law is written, there is no doubt this will lead to a ripple effect to all types of performances.

Rocky Horror came during a time where being LGBTQ+ wasn't accepted, but that didn't stop Richard O'Brien. Florida's Protection of Children law comes during a time of political attacks against the LGBTQ+ by our state's leadership, but that won't stop us.

We know this will make booking shows more difficult, but we want you to know just how hard our cast is working to make sure there will always be a place for Rocky Horror in Florida. Unfortunately, that means we will be restricting our shows to 18+. 

Rocky Horror is a community. You belong here.

Drag is not a crime.💋
Trans is not a crime.🏳️‍⚧️
SAY GAY.🏳️‍🌈
You are loved.🫂
Check your voter status.✊

Florida is becoming an increasingly unsafe state for the LGBTQ+ community. Here are just a few reasons why:

🏳️‍🌈 Drag bans limiting work opportunities for drag entertainers, targeting venues that host drag shows, aiming to define drag as adult entertainment, and canceling Pride events that feature drag.

🏳️‍🌈 Bathroom bans requiring people to use the bathroom corresponding to their assigned sex at birth, putting trans people in potentially dangerous situations and cis people in uncomfortable situations if they are gender nonconforming in any way), and potentially subjecting people to genital exams and/or genetic testing to prove their sex at birth if called into questioned.

🏳️‍🌈 Restrictions on trans healthcare for both minors and adults, as well as limiting the types of physicians who are able to provide HRT, effectively removing access to hormones from many trans adults who have been on them for years.

🏳️‍🌈 New legislation allowing doctors and other medical staff to deny treatment or services based on their personal opinions and beliefs.

🏳️‍🌈 Strict rules against discussing gender identity or sexual orientation in a classroom setting for grades K-12, as well as requiring school staff to out LGBTQ+ students to their parents upon request.

🏳️‍🌈 A rapidly increasing environment of fear and hatred toward the LGBTQ+ community and the unfounded labeling of drag entertainers as gr00mers and ped0philes, which is especially dangerous as open carry is now legal and legislators continue to fight for looser gun control.

And before you say "well why don't you and your friends just leave" - We are trying. Moving, especially to another state, is expensive and difficult. We have leases to ride out, licenses and certificates that are only valid in Florida, and lives that may not be ready to uproot just yet.
